Mr Toromo made headlines in 2010 after he killed a man using a poisoned arrow. Baringo County's chief officer in charge of Health was on Thursday arraigned at the Kabarnet Law Courts after allegedly threatening to assault and kill the devolved unit's payroll manager.
Dr Gideon Toromo denied the charges and has been released on Sh70,000 bond and cash bail of Sh50,000.
The medic, who is alleged to be suffering from a chronic psychiatric disorder (paranoid schizophrenia), made headlines in 2010 after he killed a secondary school tutor, Daniel Waweru Karanja, using a poisoned arrow.



