Today, the court was told that on November 25,2020 at the County Governor's office in Kabarnet, without lawful excuse, he uttered words "Ayabei leo nitakumaliza", which was taken as a threat to kill the county's payroll manager Francis Kibinei Ayabei.
He is also charged with a second count of causing bodily harm, contrary to section 251 of the Penal Code.



